In Week 38, the story is not of a single break but of many joints under strain. The same themes repeat in different rooms of government: force used where persuasion once sufficed, law bent toward enemies and away from friends, information shaped to protect power rather than to inform the public. Yet the Democracy Clock does not move forward this week. It holds at 7:59 p.m., even as the underlying minute hand ticks a fraction closer to midnight. That stillness reflects a balance of harms and checks: an executive pressing the outer edge of its reach, and courts and states that, for now, still push back.\
