Federalism, too, was tested. The administration\'92s deployments and rhetoric fell hardest on Democratic-led jurisdictions. Illinois and Chicago were described as sites of \'93lawlessness\'94 and \'93rebellion,\'94 justifying Guard deployments and aggressive immigration raids. Trump went on social media to call for the jailing of Governor Pritzker and Mayor Brandon Johnson, accusing them of failing to protect ICE officers. He suggested that federal troops might appear at polling places in future elections, a possibility Pritzker publicly warned about. The Office of Management and Budget, under Russ Vought, used the government shutdown to cancel funding for energy projects, climate work, and transportation infrastructure in Democratic states and cities, while threatening cuts to \'93popular Democrat programs.\'94 OMB also issued a memo questioning whether furloughed workers were guaranteed back pay, despite a 2019 law, and quietly revised guidance to remove references to that guarantee. Trump himself suggested that only some furloughed employees deserved back pay, based on merit. In this pattern, federal power is not neutral. It is aimed.\
